, affects their interpersonal relations and cultural identification. Taking on crucial topics stirred by Russian aggression that began in 2014, the novel stands out for the innovative and probing manner in which it dissects them, while providing a fresh Donbas perspective on Ukrainian identity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aIdentity (Psychology)vFiction2DLC. 0aIdentity (Psychology)vFiction. 0aLanguage and languagesvFiction2DLC. 0aLanguage and languagesvFiction. 0aMemoryvFiction2DLC. 0aMemoryvFiction. 0aRusso-Ukrainian War, 2014-vFiction. 0aUkraine Conflict, 2014-vFiction2DLC. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Russian & Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh1 aAndryczyk, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishz978311099375208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022z9783110993738oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHarvard University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311078579140uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674271760?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674271760423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674271760/original  a978-3-11-078579-1  Harvard University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099375-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishb2022  a978-3-11-099389-9  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishb2022  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2022  aZDB-23-DKUb2022